Subject: [ghostium] Canvas 2D readback hook

Spec-D wiring. Inserts a comment-marker anchor at the top of
``canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc`` so rebase tooling can locate the
hook site. The actual call into
``FingerprintNoiseSource::ApplyCanvas2DNoise`` is done at the end of
the readback paths (toDataURL / toBlob / getImageData); those edits
are line-number-dependent and refresh on every UC bump, so they live
as overlay-owned sidecar code that the apply step splices in.

Per plan.md section 4.6, the noise is a deterministic ±1 LSB
perturbation on the R, G, B channels keyed by the profile's
``canvas_seed``. Alpha is untouched. Non-Ghostium contexts pass
through unchanged (R16).

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc
